 <br>
 7> In how many ways can a CSS be integrated as a web page? 
 <br>
 <br>
 ===>  CSS can be added to HTML documents in 3 ways: Inline - by using the style attribute inside HTML elements. Internal - by using a &lt;style> element in the &lt;head> section.
   <ol start="1">
    <li>Inline - by using the style attribute inside HTML elements</li>
    <li>Internal - by using a &lt;style> element in the &lt;head> section</li>
    <li>External - by using a &lt;link> element to link to an external CSS file</li>
   </ol>
<br>
<br>

<hr>

<br>
<br>
8> Create simple three pages using External CSS, Internal CSS, and Inline CSS.
<br>
<br>
1. External - by using a &lt;link> element to link to an external CSS file

Syntax:
<br>
<div class="box4">
    &lt;head><br>
    &nbsp;&nbsp; &lt;link rel="stylesheet" <br>
    &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; type="text/css" href="style.css"><br>
  &lt;/head>
</div>
<br>
<br>
2. Internal - by using a &lt;style> element in the &lt;head> section
Syntax:
<br>
<div class="box4">
    &lt;style> <br>
    &nbsp; &nbsp; // CSS Properties <br>
    &lt;/style> <br>
</div>
 <br>
 <br>
 3. Inline - by using the style attribute inside HTML elements
 Syntax:
<br>
<div class="box4">
    &lt;p style="css_styles"> <br>
    &nbsp; &nbsp;// Content <br>
    &lt;/p> <br>
</div>
<br>
<br>
  
